<li id="cite_note-97"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-97">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFSheinkin2010" class="citation book cs1">Sheinkin, Steve (2010). "The Floating Vulture". <i><a href="/wiki/The_Notorious_Benedict_Arnold" title="The Notorious Benedict Arnold">The Notorious Benedict Arnold</a></i> (First ed.). <a href="/wiki/Square_Fish" class="mw-redirect" title="Square Fish">Square Fish</a>. p.&#160;259. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-250-02460-2" title="Special:BookSources/978-1-250-02460-2"><bdi>978-1-250-02460-2</bdi></a>. <q>"Many others struck the sails, rigging, and boats on deck," said a British officer aboard the <i>Vulture</i>. "Captain Sutherland is the only person hurt, and he very slightly on the nose by a splinter." But it was a splinter that changed the course of history. The captain ordered the <i>Vulture</i> to drop back out of range of American guns.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=The+Floating+Vulture&amp;rft.btitle=The+Notorious+Benedict+Arnold&amp;rft.pages=259&amp;rft.edition=First&amp;rft.pub=Square+Fish&amp;rft.date=2010&amp;rft.isbn=978-1-250-02460-2&amp;rft.aulast=Sheinkin&amp;rft.aufirst=Steve&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABenedict+Arnold" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
