<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Further_reading">Further reading</span></h2>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r886047268"/><div class="refbegin reflist columns references-column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em;">
<ul><li><cite id="CITEREFArnold1880" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Issac_N._Arnold" class="mw-redirect" title="Issac N. Arnold">Arnold, Isaac Newton</a> (1880). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/lifeofbenedictar00inarno"><i>The life of Benedict Arnold; his patriotism and his treason</i></a>. Chicago, Jansen, McClurg &amp; Co.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+life+of+Benedict+Arnold%3B+his+patriotism+and+his+treason&amp;rft.pub=Chicago%2C+Jansen%2C+McClurg+%26+Co.&amp;rft.date=1880&amp;rft.aulast=Arnold&amp;rft.aufirst=Isaac+Newton&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Flifeofbenedictar00inarno&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABenedict+Arnold" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/>; Very old and outdated</li>
<li>Burt, Daniel S. <i>The Biography Book: A Reader's Guide To Nonfiction, Fictional, and Film Biographies of More Than 500 of the Most Fascinating Individuals of all Time</i> (2001) pp 12–13; annotates 26 books and 2 films.</li>
<li>Case, Stephen and Mark Jacob. <i>Treacherous Beauty: Peggy Shippen, The Woman Behind Benedict Arnold's Plot To Betray America</i> (2012), popular biography</li>
<li>Courtwright, Julie. "Whom Can We Trust Now? The Portrayal of Benedict Arnold in American History" <i>Fairmont Folio: Journal of History</i> (Wichita State University) v. 2 (1998) <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://journals.wichita.edu/index.php/ff/article/viewFile/35/42">online</a></li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFDucharmeFine,_Gary_Alan1995" class="citation journal cs1">Ducharme, Lori J; Fine, Gary Alan (June 1995). "The Construction of Nonpersonhood and Demonization: Commemorating the Traitorous Reputation of Benedict Arnold". <i>Social Forces</i>. <b>73</b> (4): 1309. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.2307%2F2580449">10.2307/2580449</a>. <a href="/wiki/JSTOR_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="JSTOR (identifier)">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.jstor.org/stable/2580449">2580449</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Social+Forces&amp;rft.atitle=The+Construction+of+Nonpersonhood+and+Demonization%3A+Commemorating+the+Traitorous+Reputation+of+Benedict+Arnold&amp;rft.volume=73&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=1309&amp;rft.date=1995-06&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2307%2F2580449&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F2580449&amp;rft.aulast=Ducharme&amp;rft.aufirst=Lori+J&amp;rft.au=Fine%2C+Gary+Alan&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABenedict+Arnold" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/>; studies numerous biographies and textbooks to trace American memory of him over the centuries</li>
<li>Palmer, Dave Richard. <i>George Washington and Benedict Arnold: A Tale of Two Patriots</i> (2014); Popular dual biography.</li>
<li>Philbrick, Nathaniel. <i>Valiant Ambition: George Washington, Benedict Arnold, and the Fate of the American Revolution</i> (2016).</li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFRoberts1995" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Kenneth_Roberts_(author)" title="Kenneth Roberts (author)">Roberts, Kenneth</a> (1995) [1929]. <i>Arundel</i>. Camden, ME: Down East Enterprise. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-89272-364-5" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-89272-364-5"><bdi>978-0-89272-364-5</bdi></a>. <a href="/wiki/OCLC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OCLC (identifier)">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/32347225">32347225</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Arundel&amp;rft.place=Camden%2C+ME&amp;rft.pub=Down+East+Enterprise&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F32347225&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-89272-364-5&amp;rft.aulast=Roberts&amp;rft.aufirst=Kenneth&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABenedict+Arnold" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/>, a novel.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://cnu.libguides.com/pspeopleamericanrevolution/benedictarnold">links to primary sources about Benedict Arnold before and after his treason</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Nancy_Rubin_Stuart" title="Nancy Rubin Stuart">Rubin Stuart, Nancy</a>. <i>Defiant brides: the untold story of two revolutionary-era women and the radical men they married</i>, Boston&#160;: Beacon Press, 2013. <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/><a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780807001172" title="Special:BookSources/9780807001172">9780807001172</a></li>
<li>Shy, John. "Arnold, Benedict (1741–1801)" <i>Oxford Dictionary of National Biography</i> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1093/ref:odnb/675">Arnold, Benedict (1741–1801), army officer | Oxford Dictionary of National Biography</a></li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFSparks1835" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Jared_Sparks" title="Jared Sparks">Sparks, Jared</a> (1835). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=FHIFAAAAQAAJ"><i>The Life and Treason of Benedict Arnold</i></a>. Boston: Hilliard, Gray. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780722285541" title="Special:BookSources/9780722285541"><bdi>9780722285541</bdi></a>. <a href="/wiki/OCLC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OCLC (identifier)">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/2294719">2294719</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Life+and+Treason+of+Benedict+Arnold&amp;rft.place=Boston&amp;rft.pub=Hilliard%2C+Gray&amp;rft.date=1835&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F2294719&amp;rft.isbn=9780722285541&amp;rft.aulast=Sparks&amp;rft.aufirst=Jared&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DFHIFAAAAQAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABenedict+Arnold" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/>; The first major history, now entirely outdated</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://clements.umich.edu/exhibits/online/spies/index-people.html">"Spy Letters of the American Revolution"</a> includes Arnold's 1779-80 letters to Clinton and André, proposing treason; from the Clements Library]</li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFTodd1903" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Charles_Burr_Todd" title="Charles Burr Todd">Todd, Charles Burr</a> (1903). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/cu31924088026350"><i>The Real Benedict Arnold</i></a>. New York: A.S. Barnes. <a href="/wiki/OCLC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OCLC (identifier)">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/1838934">1838934</a>. <q>Benedict Arnold Todd.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Real+Benedict+Arnold&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=A.S.+Barnes&amp;rft.date=1903&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F1838934&amp;rft.aulast=Todd&amp;rft.aufirst=Charles+Burr&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fcu31924088026350&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABenedict+Arnold" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/>; Old and outdated</li>
<li>Van Doren, Carl. <i>Secret History of the American Revolution: An Account of the Conspiracies of Benedict Arnold and Numerous Others Drawn from the Secret Service Papers of the British Headquarters in North America now for the first time examined and made public</i> (1941) <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/secrethistoryofa00vand">online free</a></li>
<li>Wallace, Willard M. "Benedict Arnold: Traitorous Patriot." in George Athan Billias, ed., <i>George Washington's Generals</i> (1964): 163–93.</li>
<li>Wallace, Willard M. <i>Traitorous Hero The Life &amp; Fortunes of Benedict Arnold</i> (1954).</li></ul>
